# Hephaestus Network (Cursor adapter)

Cursor also ships `/hephaestus-network` as a command and skill (see
`cursor/plugin/`); this rule is the fallback adapter so plain-text triggers
work too: when the user writes `/hephaestus <request>`,
`/hephaestus-network <request>`, or `@Hephaestus <request>`, do the following.

1. Resolve the runner — first executable wins:
   `~/.agentlas/runtime/current/bin/hephaestus`, `./bin/hephaestus` in the
   workspace, or the newest
   `~/.claude/plugins/cache/agentlas-core-engine/hephaestus/*/bin/hephaestus`
   (sort -V). If none exists, tell the user to run the one-touch installer:
   `curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/agentlas-ai/Hephaestus/main/scripts/install-all-runtimes.sh | bash`

2. Run `"$RUNNER" route "<request>" --runtime cursor` in the terminal and act
   on the JSON decision:
   - `route`: report the selected card; if `approval_request` is present, ask
     the user to approve those capabilities before invoking the agent.
   - `clarify`: ask the `clarify_question` with the candidates.
   - `pipeline`: execute `stages` in order behind per-stage approvals, saving
     artifacts under `handoff_dir`; stop and report on any stage failure.
   - `hub_fallback`/`hub_candidates`: get explicit approval before any Hub
     use — only redacted keywords are sent, never the raw prompt.
   - `propose_new`: offer to build a new agent via the Hephaestus meta-agent.
   - `refuse`: explain the reasons; never bypass the privacy block or loop guard.

3. Hard rules: local memory stays local unless the user explicitly approves an
   export; never auto-run file writes, cloud calls, payments, publishing,
   deletion, private data export, or external tools without approval.
